Linux vs Windows
Linux is an open-source operating system, while Windows is paid and closed-source.
Linux is more secure and stable, while Windows is more user-friendly.
Linux uses command line and GUI, while Windows mainly uses GUI.
Linux is mostly used for servers and development, while Windows is used for personal computers.

CLI vs GUI (Short & Simple)
CLI (Command Line Interface):
User interacts using text commands. It is faster, uses less memory, and is mainly used by developers and system administrators.
GUI (Graphical User Interface):
User interacts using icons, buttons, and windows. It is easy to use and suitable for beginners.

Linux Server vs Windows Server
Linux Server is open-source and free, while Windows Server is paid.
Linux Server is more stable and secure, while Windows Server is easy to manage.
Linux Server mainly uses CLI, while Windows Server mainly uses GUI.
Linux Server is widely used for web servers and cloud, while Windows Server is used in enterprise environments.
